- 'Active participants' are those whose status is 'active';
- 'Completed more than five rounds' means they have participated in more than 5 rounds;
- 'Average scores' are calculated by averaging the scores from rounds 1 to 12.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM participants 
WHERE total_score > (SELECT AVG(total_score) FROM participants);

external_knowledge:
- 'Challenge' rounds have a higher weight in the scoring system;
- The total score is calculated by summing up the scores for all rounds, with adjustments for 'Challenge' rounds;
- The participant with the highest total score is considered the top performer.

- 'Challenge round type' corresponds to `round_type = 1`;
- 'Active participants' refers to participants with `status = 'active'`;
- The average score comparison ensures that only participants who perform better than the average of the round are included.

- 'Advanced warriors' refers to participants in the 'advanced' category;
- 'Initial challenge' refers to the first round (round_number = 1);
- 'Securing more than one victory' means having more than one score entry in the first round.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT participant_id
FROM round_scores
WHERE CAST(REPLACE(score, '"', '') AS REAL) >= 10;

external_knowledge:
- "Second round" refers to the round number 2;
- "Average score" is calculated by averaging the scores of all rounds for each participant;
- "Type of round" includes categories such as quiz, challenge, or test.

- "shining stars" refers to participants with the highest performance scores;
- "peak performance" is calculated as the score divided by the product of the difficulty level and the time taken, rounded to two decimal places;
- The performance score reflects how well a participant did relative to the difficulty and time spent.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT participant_id) 
FROM round_scores 
WHERE attempts > 1;

SELECT round_number, AVG(score) AS average_score
FROM round_scores
GROUP BY round_number;

